BENIN – Chief Bolaji Anani, National President of the Nigerian Red Cross Society (NRCS), has disclosed in Benin City, the Edo State capital, that the society lost seven of its members to bomb blast in the North East zone of the country, while rendering their humanitarian services. Anani made the disclosure at the Annual General Meeting of the Edo State branch of the society, which also witnessed the election and inauguration of a new executive that would pilot the affairs of the body for the next four years. According to the National President, ” We had a terrible situation in the North Eastern part of the country where we lost no fewer than seven of our members to bomb blasts. Besides, two ladies were also taken captive and were later found to have been killed by eastern terrorist groups.